Cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) have been confirmed in Micronesia. The authorities have introduced a number of measures to limit the spread of the virus.
The situation may change rapidly, including in neighbouring countries. Follow local guidance at all times.
We advise all non-resident British nationals to leave, and for resident British nationals to be aware of border closures and maintain contact with travel providers on flight restrictions. See Return to the UK.
Federated States of Micronesia FSM has declared a “state of public health emergency” and has banned travellers who have travelled via China since 6 Jan. There are further requirements for travellers from countries with cases of coronavirus to spend 14 days in a country without cases.
You should comply with any additional screening measures put in place by the Federated States of Micronesia authorities. Further advice is available from Public Health England, and the TravelHealthPro website.
